liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: England are batting on here this morning, Stuart Broad resuming on 2 and Anderson on 8. Broad, helmet off, leads Jimmy Anderson (helmet on) down the stairs and then walks through the guard of honour on his own. It's the last time these two will play together - the 138th and final Test of Broad and Anderson in tandem. That's a really nice touch from the Aussies. There is a huge ovation from the crowd, who have not stopped applauding. I imagine the sporting reception will be shelved pretty quickly now as hostilities resume, with a short-ball field in place.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Australia gives Stuart Broad guard of honour
